-- NTPC Shares Drop Most in a Month After Profit Declines on Cost Increases
-- Rakteem Katakey
-- 2010-07-27T03:39:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-27/ntpc-shares-drop-most-in-a-month-after-profit-declines-on-cost-increases.html

          
          
             Shares of NTPC Ltd. declined after
profit at Asiaâ€™s second-largest power producer by market value
unexpectedly declined.  
 The stock fell as much as 1.4 percent to 198.85 rupees in
Mumbai, the most in a month, and traded at 199.15 rupees at 9:04
a.m local time.  
 Net income in the three months ended June 30 dropped 16.1
percent to 18.4 billion rupees, the company said in a filing
yesterday after trading ended.  
